BLOCKED: target-side Buildroot e1-npu-ml-smoke transcript is missing.

reason: /usr/bin/e1-npu-ml-smoke opens /dev/e1-npu and drives a real GEMM_S8
  tile through the e1 NPU ioctl ABI (E1_NPU_IOC_GET_CONTRACT,
  E1_NPU_IOC_RUN_CMD RELU4_S8, E1_NPU_IOC_RUN_GEMM_S8, E1_NPU_IOC_GET_COUNTERS),
  rejecting any CPU-only fallback and requiring the hardware to return the
  reference result [[-44,8],[139,-54]]. This needs the eliza,e1-npu MMIO
  register block at E1_NPU_BASE=0x10020000 to exist and execute the workload.
  No available simulation target models the e1 NPU: qemu-system-riscv64 -M virt
  has no eliza,e1-npu device, and the Renode platform
  (sim/renode/eliza_e1.repl) models only CPU, RAM, UART, PLIC, and CLINT. The
  smoke therefore cannot PASS without e1 silicon, an e1 NPU QEMU device model,
  or an RTL co-simulation that implements the NPU register block.

required capture command (on a target that exposes /dev/e1-npu):
  E1_NPU_ML_SMOKE_CMD='ssh root@TARGET /usr/bin/e1-npu-ml-smoke --device /dev/e1-npu --workload gemm_s8_int8_2x2x3 --require-npu' \
    sw/buildroot/scripts/capture-buildroot-evidence.sh /path/to/buildroot ml-smoke

required validation command:
  python3 scripts/check_software_bsp.py buildroot --require-evidence

This marker is not release evidence. Replace it only with a real transcript at
docs/evidence/buildroot/e1-npu-ml-smoke.log captured from a target or simulator
that actually instantiates the eliza,e1-npu platform device and executes the
GEMM_S8 workload in hardware.
